I'm so sad with the change in ownership. The menu may be similar but the quality of food, thoughtfulness and taste just isn't the same. Perhaps they tried to make it up in quantity? We got our usual Outter Reef burritos which, upon reading the menu, was described to have green sauce. I ordered it as described ("your protein, lettuce, beans, rice and green sauce") with carnitas. The cashier then asked if I wanted to make it wet. But it comes with green sauce, I said. Oh, no, she told me, there is no green sauce - that's a dollar extra. But it's on the menu, I reply. No, that's wrong, she insisted. Yes, make it wet. Ok, do you want red or green sauce? <sigh> Green, please. Next up hubs orders his outter reef burrito with chicken. Do you want to make it wet? Yes. Did you want to keep the sour cream and guac in it?, she asks. No sour cream for hubs.  Wait.Whatthehell? Is my burrito coming with sour cream and guac I didn't want that was clearly posted as an extra charge? Next up the wait. We sit at a table near the cashier/kitchen where one of the back of the house seems to be having a family crisis with his apparent wife - this obviously doesn't happen on the daily, but it was weird they didn't go outside. It took a while, but then I realized it was because they were creating burritos the size of an enlarged liver (look it up, they're huge). Mine was marked with a slash of sour cream - the universal indicator you're about to eat something you didn't order.  We asked the lady who brought the food about the mystery that is the green sauce listed in the outter reef burrito description. She (seemingly inaccurately) explained the green sauce was inside the burrito. But yes, if we wanted to put the sauce on the outside it would cost more. Did I just order a burrito from Medicare? Does it matter WHERE the sauce is on the plate when you decide whether to charge or not?  I can't imagine the charge if we asked for it on the side. Ok so let's get on with eating this burrito I've been jonesing for. Wheres the meat? This is a rice and bean roll! With sour cream and guac! Oh well, may as well make the most of all this green sauce. I finally discover a ball of carnitas hiding in the corner of the butt of the burrito, 6 spoonfuls of rice too late. Maybe these are just hiccups the new team has to iron out? Either way, I may have to look for a new burrito joint in town.
